description: 'TIAMAT,' Part Four The epic battle between Sara Pezzini, bearer of the Witchblade, and Tiamat, the ancient Babylonian Queen-Goddess culminates in an earth-shaking showdown! The ongoing team of RON MARZ (Artifacts, Magdalena) and STJEPAN SEJIC (Angelus) inch closer to the huge anniversary #150 issue!
name: Tiamat, Part 4 of 4

description: Final Season
name: Stagione Finale

description: "Ode for a world never born"
name: Ode per un mondo mai Nato

description: "We weren't created to be brutes" a verse from Dante Alighieri's "Inferno".
name: Fatti non fummo per venir come Bruti...

description: "Waiting for John Doe" final volume of the original series. Continues in the new series.
name: Aspettando John Doe

description: Mike is tortured by being hung upside down from a flying helicopter over a horde of zombies. Moloch wants answers to what Mike knows about the gateway portal and King Zombie. In the prison camp a sadistic fighter nicknamed Wolverine tears up zombies in an arena and demands a tougher challenge. Dan and John find a way out of their warehouse prison via an air duct. As King Zombie watches the helicopter, he is also trailing Deake's footprints. But he is stunned when the footprints suddenly disappear. And unfortunately two of our favorite teens meet their demise in this issue.
name: Give 'Em Enough Rope

description: King Zombie and the Grakken demon creatures attack Moloch's helicopter and manage to damage the blades, forcing the copter to the ground. The zombies move in for the kill as the survivors attempt to escape but their numbers are dwindling.
name: All Cats In the Dark Are Black

description: Moloch's mistress, Reyna, forces Wolverine to release Dan and she takes him to her quarters. King Zombie receives a report of Moloch's military city from other intelligent zombies. Dan overhears the talk of the mission and realizes that Mike is dead. Moloch realizes that zombies are making a coordinated attack against his city and mobilizes his forces, unaware of what Reyna is up to. Moloch has ordered all of the prisoners in the warehouse to be set free...to provide a distraction and food for the invading zombies.
name: Un-Dead Force

description: The carnage is widespread as Moloch's city is under full-scale zombie attack. Joey finally gets his chance to kill zombies and makes the most of it as he meets up with Dan. They realize that Donna is missing and decide to search for her. But with the over-whelming number of zombies, Dan reluctantly decides that he will never find her and leaves the city by motorcycle with Joey in toe. During the battle, a wandering Deake is captured by Reyna and an injured Moloch while Bowker is left behind. The battle is over and the zombies have captured the city for King Zombie.
name: Bleeding Hearts In Hand

description: Donna and Percy are captured by a roving motorcycle gang of humans. Donna is raped but Percy, being an imbecile, is left alone. Dan and Joey are shocked when they are discovered by zombies while hiding out. To their surprise, they find out that the zombies aren't attacking, just walking right past them and they decide to follow the mindless horde. In the conquered city, King Zombie discovers that all of his zombie troops are abruptly leaving...as if following some magical calling. Dan and Joey come upon the Voodoo Queen who seems to not only be controlling the zombie masses but now King Zombie as well.
name: Better Harms and Gnawing

description: After Dan and Joey have left their city, we find out that the community was over-run by the zombies with few survivors. Meanwhile Wayne provides a service of cleaning out houses of zombies for ammo and food in a small village. And Kirk finds an ingenious way to escape a group of nearby zombies.

Orchid befriends a young rebel, Simon, who aims to save his fellow rebels and all of the oppressed people of the land. To do so, he must escape, so he, Orchid, and her brother hatch an escape plan, but find themselves in unfamiliar territory.

Four page preview comic that was bound in to Fleetway boys comics (cover dated 16 September 1989). It included painted artwork throughout by Ian Kennedy.

Ring Raiders issue one launched the following week.
name: Ring Raiders mini-comic

description:
Until recently, Zoey Redbird was an average high-school student worrying about grades, boys, and breakouts. But priorities have a way of changing when you are marked as a vampyre, enroll in the vampyre academy House of Night, and have to figure out a whole new social hierarchy, affinities for elemental magic, and physiological changes that make you crave blood.

Beginning a series of comic book adaptations of the House of Night series of vampire novels, this issue picks up partway through the action. This and immediately upcoming issues take place between scenes from the second novel, Betrayed.
name: House of Night

With the exception of 'The Thirteenth Floor', all the stories come to an end in time for the merger with Tiger comic next issue.

After 46 chapters, Monster is finally wrapped up. The story started in Scream! comic (originally written by Alan Moore), before moving over to Eagle when the two comics merged (in issue 128). The final Scream! story to survive - 'The Thirteenth Floor' remained a fixture of Eagle until issue 258 (cover dated 28 February 1987), at which point Max is shipped off to IPC where he becomes Eagle's editor.

The Fists of Danny Pyke, another long running series (the first episode was in issue 79) also comes to an end after more than seventy episodes, with Danny retiring as World Champion. Illustrated by John Burns for most of its run, the final three parts were drawn by Jose Gual.

Finally, after 30 blood-soaked episodes, Bloodfang ends with the tyrannosaur returned to his own time.

Milestone issue before the issue 259 relaunch. All the stories (bar Death Wish, which starts a new story this week) are wrapped up. Dan Dare is killed (by Dargath), Doomlord beats Kev and Shal (the Lord and Lady of Doom), Clovis and Chowdhary finish off the Blind-man and after a three year run (and 146 episodes), Max the Computer's adventures on The Thirteenth Floor come to a close with Maxwell Towers burning down and Max shipped off to IPC Magazines where he becomes the editor of Eagle.
